Adding simple: Paragraph 
...obj is  This is solely based on **Existence Dependency**. A true dependent entity cannot logically exist without the related parent entity. For instance, an Order Item cannot exist without an Order. If removing the parent entity logically implies removing the dependent entity, then it is a dependent entity.

Found codeblocks  0
...contenth for prose html is...
<div>
 <p>
  This is solely based on
  <strong>
   Existence Dependency
  </strong>
  . A true dependent entity cannot logically exist without the related parent entity. For instance, an Order Item cannot exist without an Order. If removing the parent entity logically implies removing the dependent entity, then it is a dependent entity.
 </p>
</div>

Adding simple: Paragraph 
...obj is  This is solely based on **Existence Dependency**. A true dependent entity cannot logically exist without the related parent entity. For instance, an Order Item cannot exist without an Order. If removing the parent entity logically implies removing the dependent entity, then it is a dependent entity.

Found codeblocks  0
...contenth for prose html is...
<div>
 <p>
  This is solely based on
  <strong>
   Existence Dependency
  </strong>
  . A true dependent entity cannot logically exist without the related parent entity. For instance, an Order Item cannot exist without an Order. If removing the parent entity logically implies removing the dependent entity, then it is a dependent entity.
 </p>
</div>

Adding simple: Paragraph 
...obj is  This is solely based on **Existence Dependency**. A true dependent entity cannot logically exist without the related parent entity. For instance, an Order Item cannot exist without an Order. If removing the parent entity logically implies removing the dependent entity, then it is a dependent entity.

Found codeblocks  0
...contenth for prose html is...
<div>
 <p>
  This is solely based on
  <strong>
   Existence Dependency
  </strong>
  . A true dependent entity cannot logically exist without the related parent entity. For instance, an Order Item cannot exist without an Order. If removing the parent entity logically implies removing the dependent entity, then it is a dependent entity.
 </p>
</div>

Adding simple: Paragraph 
...obj is  In Literate Data Modeling, the main components of interest are typically Classes, Attributes, Models, and Subjects. However, to streamline the model and promote reusability, we introduce a supertype called Component. By defining common attributes and behaviors in the Component class, we can inherit them in the subclasses, ensuring consistency and reducing duplication throughout the model.

Found codeblocks  0
...contenth for prose html is...
<div>
 <p>
  In Literate Data Modeling, the main components of interest are typically Classes, Attributes, Models, and Subjects. However, to streamline the model and promote reusability, we introduce a supertype called Component. By defining common attributes and behaviors in the Component class, we can inherit them in the subclasses, ensuring consistency and reducing duplication throughout the model.
 </p>
</div>

...end of contenth for prose html .
Adding simple: Paragraph 
...obj is  We present the Component class first because it is a best practice in modeling to introduce supertypes before their subtypes. This approach allows readers to understand the general concepts and shared properties before delving into the specifics of each specialized component.

Found codeblocks  0
...contenth for prose html is...
<div>
 <p>
  We present the Component class first because it is a best practice in modeling to introduce supertypes before their subtypes. This approach allows readers to understand the general concepts and shared properties before delving into the specifics of each specialized component.
 </p>
</div>

Adding simple: Paragraph 
...obj is  This is solely based on **Existence Dependency**. A true dependent entity cannot logically exist without the related parent entity. For instance, an Order Item cannot exist without an Order. If removing the parent entity logically implies removing the dependent entity, then it is a dependent entity.

Found codeblocks  0
...contenth for prose html is...
<div>
 <p>
  This is solely based on
  <strong>
   Existence Dependency
  </strong>
  . A true dependent entity cannot logically exist without the related parent entity. For instance, an Order Item cannot exist without an Order. If removing the parent entity logically implies removing the dependent entity, then it is a dependent entity.
 </p>
</div>

Adding simple: Paragraph 
...obj is  This is solely based on **Existence Dependency**. A true dependent entity cannot logically exist without the related parent entity. For instance, an Order Item cannot exist without an Order. If removing the parent entity logically implies removing the dependent entity, then it is a dependent entity.

Found codeblocks  0
...contenth for prose html is...
<div>
 <p>
  This is solely based on
  <strong>
   Existence Dependency
  </strong>
  . A true dependent entity cannot logically exist without the related parent entity. For instance, an Order Item cannot exist without an Order. If removing the parent entity logically implies removing the dependent entity, then it is a dependent entity.
 </p>
</div>

Adding simple: Paragraph 
...obj is  This is solely based on **Existence Dependency**. A true dependent entity cannot logically exist without the related parent entity. For instance, an Order Item cannot exist without an Order. If removing the parent entity logically implies removing the dependent entity, then it is a dependent entity.

Found codeblocks  0
...contenth for prose html is...
<div>
 <p>
  This is solely based on
  <strong>
   Existence Dependency
  </strong>
  . A true dependent entity cannot logically exist without the related parent entity. For instance, an Order Item cannot exist without an Order. If removing the parent entity logically implies removing the dependent entity, then it is a dependent entity.
 </p>
</div>

Adding simple: Paragraph 
...obj is  This is solely based on **Existence Dependency**. A true dependent entity cannot logically exist without the related parent entity. For instance, an Order Item cannot exist without an Order. If removing the parent entity logically implies removing the dependent entity, then it is a dependent entity.

Found codeblocks  0
...contenth for prose html is...
<div>
 <p>
  This is solely based on
  <strong>
   Existence Dependency
  </strong>
  . A true dependent entity cannot logically exist without the related parent entity. For instance, an Order Item cannot exist without an Order. If removing the parent entity logically implies removing the dependent entity, then it is a dependent entity.
 </p>
</div>

</div>

Adding simple: Paragraph 
...obj is  This is solely based on **Existence Dependency**. A true dependent entity cannot logically exist without the related parent entity. For instance, an Order Item cannot exist without an Order. If removing the parent entity logically implies removing the dependent entity, then it is a dependent entity.

Found codeblocks  0
...contenth for prose html is...
<div>
 <p>
  This is solely based on
  <strong>
   Existence Dependency
  </strong>
  . A true dependent entity cannot logically exist without the related parent entity. For instance, an Order Item cannot exist without an Order. If removing the parent entity logically implies removing the dependent entity, then it is a dependent entity.
 </p>
</div>

Adding simple: Paragraph 
...obj is  This is solely based on **Existence Dependency**. A true dependent entity cannot logically exist without the related parent entity. For instance, an Order Item cannot exist without an Order. If removing the parent entity logically implies removing the dependent entity, then it is a dependent entity.

Found codeblocks  0
...contenth for prose html is...
<div>
 <p>
  This is solely based on
  <strong>
   Existence Dependency
  </strong>
  . A true dependent entity cannot logically exist without the related parent entity. For instance, an Order Item cannot exist without an Order. If removing the parent entity logically implies removing the dependent entity, then it is a dependent entity.
 </p>
</div>

Adding simple: Paragraph 
...obj is  In Literate Data Modeling, the main components of interest are typically Classes, Attributes, Models, and Subjects. However, to streamline the model and promote reusability, we introduce a supertype called Component. By defining common attributes and behaviors in the Component class, we can inherit them in the subclasses, ensuring consistency and reducing duplication throughout the model.

Found codeblocks  0
...contenth for prose html is...
<div>
 <p>
  In Literate Data Modeling, the main components of interest are typically Classes, Attributes, Models, and Subjects. However, to streamline the model and promote reusability, we introduce a supertype called Component. By defining common attributes and behaviors in the Component class, we can inherit them in the subclasses, ensuring consistency and reducing duplication throughout the model.
 </p>
</div>

...end of contenth for prose html .
Adding simple: Paragraph 
...obj is  We present the Component class first because it is a best practice in modeling to introduce supertypes before their subtypes. This approach allows readers to understand the general concepts and shared properties before delving into the specifics of each specialized component.

Found codeblocks  0
...contenth for prose html is...
<div>
 <p>
  We present the Component class first because it is a best practice in modeling to introduce supertypes before their subtypes. This approach allows readers to understand the general concepts and shared properties before delving into the specifics of each specialized component.
 </p>
</div>

...end of contenth for prose html .

Adding simple: Paragraph 
...obj is  This is solely based on **Existence Dependency**. A true dependent entity cannot logically exist without the related parent entity. For instance, an Order Item cannot exist without an Order. If removing the parent entity logically implies removing the dependent entity, then it is a dependent entity.

Found codeblocks  0
...contenth for prose html is...
<div>
 <p>
  This is solely based on
  <strong>
   Existence Dependency
  </strong>
  . A true dependent entity cannot logically exist without the related parent entity. For instance, an Order Item cannot exist without an Order. If removing the parent entity logically implies removing the dependent entity, then it is a dependent entity.
 </p>
</div>

...end of contenth for prose html .

    <p>
     Subbtypes: byBrand - Brand1, Brand2,... (non exclusive, exhaustive)
    </p>

Adding simple: Paragraph 
...obj is  This is solely based on **Existence Dependency**. A true dependent entity cannot logically exist without the related parent entity. For instance, an Order Item cannot exist without an Order. If removing the parent entity logically implies removing the dependent entity, then it is a dependent entity.

Found codeblocks  0
...contenth for prose html is...
<div>
 <p>
  This is solely based on
  <strong>
   Existence Dependency
  </strong>
  . A true dependent entity cannot logically exist without the related parent entity. For instance, an Order Item cannot exist without an Order. If removing the parent entity logically implies removing the dependent entity, then it is a dependent entity.
 </p>
</div>

...end of contenth for prose html .

Adding simple: Paragraph 
...obj is  This is solely based on **Existence Dependency**. A true dependent entity cannot logically exist without the related parent entity. For instance, an Order Item cannot exist without an Order. If removing the parent entity logically implies removing the dependent entity, then it is a dependent entity.

Found codeblocks  0
...contenth for prose html is...
<div>
 <p>
  This is solely based on
  <strong>
   Existence Dependency
  </strong>
  . A true dependent entity cannot logically exist without the related parent entity. For instance, an Order Item cannot exist without an Order. If removing the parent entity logically implies removing the dependent entity, then it is a dependent entity.
 </p>
</div>

Adding simple: Paragraph 
...obj is  ***DSL***:  Shown in the DSL as
 
+ > Subbtypes: byBrand - Brand1, Brand2,... (non exclusive, exhaustive)
